ğŸ”„ 3. Bitcoin Process (Simplified)
ğŸ”¹ a. Transaction Creation
1.	User initiates a Bitcoin transfer
2.	Transaction is signed with a private key
ğŸ”¹ b. Broadcast to Network
â€¢	The transaction is sent to Bitcoinâ€™s peer-to-peer network
ğŸ”¹ c. Verification
â€¢	Nodes verify:
o	Authentic signature
o	No double-spending
ğŸ”¹ d. Mining & Proof of Work
â€¢	Miners collect transactions in a block
â€¢	They solve a cryptographic puzzle (PoW)
â€¢	The first miner to solve it broadcasts the block
ğŸ”¹ e. Block Added to Blockchain
â€¢	Other nodes verify the block
â€¢	Once accepted, the block becomes part of the permanent ledger
ğŸ”¹ f. Reward
â€¢	Miner gets a block reward + transaction fees
ğŸ‘‰ This process secures the network and makes tampering extremely hard.
