ğŸ“Œ Quick Summary (100-Word Exam Answer)
Bitcoin is a decentralized digital currency that runs on a blockchain to allow secure, peer-to-peer value transfers without intermediaries. Its functions include being a medium of exchange, a store of value, and a unit of account. Transactions are created, broadcast, verified, and then mined into blocks through Proof of Work, adding to the blockchain ledger. In 2026, major Bitcoin mining nations include the United States (~37.5 %), Russia (~16.4 %), China (~11.7 %), Paraguay (~7.2 %), and Kazakhstan (~6.5 %). Mining distribution reflects energy costs, infrastructure, and regulatory environments globally.

